<post_id>1043330223748384</post_id>
<electoral-propaganda-analysis>
This Facebook post, promoting a professional agricultural training event ("Pro Class OPEN by AGXecutive"), does not constitute electoral propaganda.  While the post is categorized as "POLITICAL" due to its presence in Facebook's ad library, the content itself is entirely focused on promoting a training program. There is no mention of any political candidate, party, or election. The dates mentioned (14 and 15 November) are not election dates, and the call to action ("ÎNSCRIE-TE" - "Sign up") is solely related to event registration. The post's objective is to increase enrollment in the training program, not to influence voters in any election.  The image accompanying the post further reinforces this, showing only the event's branding and details.  Even though the post falls under the "POLITICAL" category in Facebook's ad library, this categorization is likely due to the broad definition of political advertising and does not automatically qualify it as electoral propaganda under Romanian law.  The lack of any reference to candidates or parties, and the clear focus on a non-political event, strongly suggests that this post does not violate Article 98 t) of LEGE nr. 208 din 20 iulie 2015.
</electoral-propaganda-analysis>
<electoral-propaganda-decision>FALSE</electoral-propaganda-decision>
<electoral-propaganda-candidates/>

<message-for-police/>
</conclusion>
</output>
